casebody.data:
Disciplinary Counsel v. Johnson.

[Cite as Disciplinary Counsel v. Johnson, 135 Ohio St.3d 1256, 2013-Ohio-684.]

(No. 2010-2199 Submitted February 26, 2013 Decided February 28, 2013.)

{¶ 1} This cause came on for further consideration upon the filing of an application for reinstatement by respondent, Frederick Bruce Johnson, Attorney Registration No. 0003093, last known business address in Marysville, Ohio.

{¶ 2} The court coming now to consider its order of March 28, 2012, wherein the court, pursuant to Gov.Bar R. V(6)(B)(3), suspended respondent for a period of two years with 18 months stayed, finds that respondent has substantially complied with that order and with the provisions of Gov.Bar R. V(10)(A).

{¶ 3} Therefore, it is ordered by this court that respondent is reinstated to the practice of law in the state of Ohio.

{¶ 4} It is further ordered that the clerk of this court issue certified copies of this order as provided for in Gov.Bar R. V(8)(D)(1), that publication be made as *1257provided for in Gov.Bar R. V(8)(D)(2), and that respondent bear the costs of publication.

O’Connor, C.J., and Pfeifer, O’Donnell, Lanzinger, Kennedy, French, and O’Neill, JJ., concur.
